content:
#
# This is a Shiny web application. You can run the application by clicking
# the 'Run App' button above.
#
# Find out more about building applications with Shiny here:
#
#    https://shiny.posit.co/
#

library(shiny)
library(apiINE)
library(dplyr)
library(xlsx)
library(ggplot2)
library(plotly)

########-----------
df<-read.csv("data_ine_municipalities.csv")

#######----------

# Define UI for application that draws a histogram
ui <- fluidPage(

    # Application title
    titlePanel("Average Monthly Salary by Portuguese Municipalities"),

    # Sidebar with a slider input for number of bins 
    sidebarLayout(
        sidebarPanel(
          sliderInput("range", "Average Salary Range:",min = 0, max = 3000, value = c(0,3000)),
          selectInput("regions","Municipalities",
                      unique(df$region), multiple = TRUE, selectize = FALSE, selected = unique(df$region), size = 20),
        ),

        # Show a plot of the generated distribution
        mainPanel(
          plotlyOutput("plot", height = 800)
        )
    )
)

# Define server logic required to draw a histogram
server <- function(input, output) {

    
  data_plot <- reactive(df %>% 
                          filter(avg_month_salary >= input$range[1] & avg_month_salary <= input$range[2]) %>%
                          filter(region %in% input$regions))
    
    


  output$plot <- renderPlotly({
    ggplotly(ggplot(data_plot(), aes(x = year, y = avg_month_salary, colour = region, group = region)) + 
      geom_line() + 
      theme_minimal() + 
      theme(legend.position = "none"), tooltip = c("colour", "y"))
  })
    
  
}

# Run the application 
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
